    Comparable<EDIFName>

    public class EDIFCell
extends EDIFPropertyObject
    Represent a logical cell in an EDIF netlist. Can be both a leaf cell or a hierarchical cell. Created on: May 11, 2017

      • addPort

        public EDIFPort addPort(EDIFPort port)
        Adds a port to the cell. Checks for naming collisions and throws RuntimeException if it occurs. Single bit ports that are not bussed, are keyed by their full name. Bussed ports, however, have their range truncated to just the opening square bracket so that the port can be retrieved from a valid EDIFPortInst name (range being unknown). For example, bus[3:0] would be keyed by "bus[".
        Parameters:
        port - The port to add.
        Returns:
        The port that was added.

      • getPort

        public EDIFPort getPort(String name)
        Gets a port by bus name (see EDIFPort.getBusName()). Multi-bit ports need to have closing square bracket and range removed (for example: "bus[3:0]" -> "bus["). See EDIFCell.addPort(EDIFPort) for more information.
        Parameters:
        name - Bus name (ends with '[' to represent a bussed port) of the port to get. Single bit ports use their entire name.
        Returns:
        The port or null if none exists.
